The paper focuses on developing a model for multilingual image search using visual object detection and diverse multi-head attention. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for textual semantics and computer vision (CV) techniques for visual objects. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new objective function and evaluates the model's performance, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal representations, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
